.TH getarg 3
.SH NAME
getarg, iargc \- return command line arguments
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
.B subroutine getarg (k, arg)
.br
.B character*(*) arg
.sp 1
.B function iargc ()
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
A call to
\*Vgetarg\*O
will return the \f3k\f2th\f1 command line argument in character string
\*Varg.\*O
The 0\f2th\f1 argument is the command name.
.PP
\*VIargc\*O
returns the index of the last command line argument.
